      "content": "The revised version is better, but mentioning \"10 participants\" right in the abstract is still going to get us rejected by Nature editors instantly. They'll see that number and think the study isn't statistically significant. Can we find a way to describe the methodology that emphasizes the depth or the complexity of the testing instead of just the raw number of people? Maybe something that implies a more substantial sample without actually lying about the number?",
